# ============================================================
# FAMILY CORE POLICY
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: policy
domain: family
scope: family.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines policy constraints for family.

## policy_rules
Family policy constrains:
- who may view family detail
- who may mutate family relation state
- which care/responsibility actions are valid
- what family history may be disclosed
- when family paths must be denied or escalated

## required_behavior
- membership scope must be explicit
- care/responsibility scope must be explicit
- disclosure scope must be explicit
- denial behavior must be explicit

## disclosure_matrix
- bounded public family summary
- member-scoped detail
- operator/reviewer detail
- historical family detail
- denied output

## allowed_denied_matrix
- allow bounded read only for valid scope
- allow mutation only for valid authority and basis
- allow historical reference only in valid mode
- deny hidden family-authority widening
- deny disclosure beyond allowed scope

## escalation_rules
If family membership,
responsibility scope,
authority,
or disclosure scope is unclear,
the family path must stop and escalate.

## review_checklist
- membership policy is explicit
- care/responsibility policy is explicit
- disclosure matrix exists
- denial behavior is explicit
